Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(halved, peeled and chopped into small pieces).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #saucepan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{240%g}(diced), onion and @sliced mushrooms{180%g} to the saucepan and stir-fry until softened, ~{5-6%minutes}. 

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, boil a full #kettle{}.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Add the garlic to the saucepan and cook ~{30%seconds}.

Add the @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, @mixed herbs{1%sachet} and @water{50%ml} for the sauce to the garlic. Stir in the @creme fraiche{75%g}.

Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g} until melted.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Meanwhile, pour the boiled water into a saucepan with @salt{1/2%tsp} and bring back to the boil.

When boiling, add the @spinach and ricotta ravioli{250%g} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{3%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{}. Drizzle with @oil{} and gently stir through to stop it sticking together.

When everything's ready, gently stir the ravioli through the creamy mushroom sauce.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed. Add a splash of water if you feel it needs it.

Share the ravioli between your #bowls{}.

Top with the @wild rocket{20%g} and finish by drizzling over the @balsamic glaze{12%ml}.

Enjoy!